\fs32 Perimeter Basics\cb1 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 Securing Your Network Perimeter
\f0\b0 \'a0 - Cybercriminals are always on the lookout for weaknesses in one\'92s network. Since companies today allow data access to several employees, partners, and consumers for efficiency, it exposes the network to multiple threats.\'a0\

\f1\b What is a Network Perimeter?
\f0\b0 \'a0 - A network perimeter is a boundary between the internal network and the Internet. It is the edge of what a company has control over. In perspective, it\'92s like a virtual wall that allows and prevents specific aspects based on rules and policies.\'a0\'a0\

\f1\b Network Perimeter includes the following:\'a0\'a0
\f0\b0 \

\f1\b Firewalls: 
\f0\b0 A firewall can either be hardware, software, or both. It serves as the first line of defense in network security wherein it monitors inbound and outbound network traffic and decides whether to block or allow it based on security policies.\'a0\'a0\
Some types of firewalls include:\'a0\'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\li1440\fi-480\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f2\fs26\fsmilli13333 \cf2 \'e1
\f0\fs18\fsmilli9333 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 
\fs32 Proxy firewall\'a0\

\f2\fs26\fsmilli13333 \'e1
\f0\fs18\fsmilli9333 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 
\fs32 Stateful Inspection Firewall\'a0\

\f2\fs26\fsmilli13333 \'e1
\f0\fs18\fsmilli9333 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 
\fs32 Unified Threat Management Firewall\'a0\

\f2\fs26\fsmilli13333 \'e1
\f0\fs18\fsmilli9333 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0 
\fs32 Virtual Firewall\'a0\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa320\partightenfactor0

\f1\b \cf2 Importance of Network Perimeter
\f0\b0 \'a0 - In today\'92s business environment, we rely heavily on our devices to stay connected and our dependence on network security has increased due to the growing number of cyberattacks. However, as businesses expand, so are the location and the addition of devices and many of which are being used outside the network perimeter, then, presents a problem when it comes to security.\'a0\'a0\
Since most people can now work anywhere, data can be shared and collected on a massive scale and the security team\'92s capacity to monitor all these data could be out of control. The concept of network perimeter will allow your organization to think strategically about how you can protect critical internal data from external threats.\'a0\'a0\
\'a0\
\'a0\
\'a0\
So, how can you secure your network perimeter?\'a0\'a0\
